Class = Variables and Objects.

Variables
- Declaration
  -Type and Name 
  -Initializing - Assigning a Value
-Assignment
  - = is the simplest one
    - assigns a value to the variable.
  - rules:
      - int assigned to float, or any larger data type with be automatically converted into a float
      - short, byte and other smaller data types used with an operator are automatically converted into an int. 
- Compound Assignment
  - simplifies assignment and operator
    - *=, +=, -=,/=, %=
      - also takes away the need for casting
